    "abstract": "<jats:p>This paper considers maximum likelihood (ML) estimation in a large class of models with hidden Markov regimes. We investigate consistency of the ML estimator and local asymptotic normality for the models under general conditions, which allow for autoregressive dynamics in the observable process, Markov regime sequences with covariate\u2010dependent transition matrices, and possible model misspecification. A Monte Carlo study examines the finite\u2010sample properties of the ML estimator in correctly specified and misspecified models. An empirical application is also discussed.</jats:p>",
